ont-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Further to your letter of 23 October 2013, I am enclosing hyperlinks to HM Revenue &amp; Customs’ published data on each of the three taxes identified by the National Audit Office (NAO), namely Stamp Duty Land Tax, Inheritance Tax and Capital Gains Tax.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Published estimates of Exchequer receipts from 1999-2000 to 2012-13 split between the four countries in the UK for individual taxes including IHT, CGT and SDLT are available on the HMRC website at: </span><a href="http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistics/receipts/disagg-stats.pdf"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistic</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">s/receipts/disagg-stats.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> with further details about the methodologies used at </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a href="http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistics/receipts/disagg-method.pdf"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistics/receipts/disagg-method.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The data we publish for each tax is slightly different, depending on the tax and below are the relevant links by tax.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Stamp</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Duty</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Land</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> Tax (SDLT)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">HMRC publishes property data based on SDLT returns in three main publications:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:8.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">A monthly release detailing the monthly number of residential and non-residential property transactions, split by country back to 2005 (</span><a href="http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistics/transactions/val-40000-or-above.pdf"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistics/transac</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">t</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">ions/val-40000-or-above.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:8.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">An annual, calendar year release detailing the number and value of residential and non-residential property transactions. This provides breakdowns by region and price band back to 2005 (</span><a href="http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistics/transactions/annual-transactions.pdf"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistics/transactions/annual-transactions.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:8.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">An annual, financial year release detailing the number of residential/non-residential transactions and the total SDLT collected, with breakdowns by SDLT rate band, region, local authority, and parliamentary constituency. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">(</span><a href="http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistics/stamp-duty/stamp-tax-sep13.pdf"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistics/stamp-duty/stamp-tax-sep13.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The first two publications are based on the date the property transaction was completed, whereas the third is based upon the date HMRC issued an SDLT certificate (i.e. after a correct return was received).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Inheritance Tax (IHT)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Our latest published estimate for the number of estates passing on death in </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Scotland</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> with IHT liabilities is around 1,000 for 2010-11 deaths. This estimate has been published on the HMRC website at </span><a href="http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistics/inheritance/table12-11.pdf"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistics/inheritance/table12-11.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Although we have not published any regional estimates for the values of IHT reliefs/exemptions, HMRC’s latest UK-wide estimates of some of the main IHT reliefs/exemptions for estates passing on death in 2010-11 are published at </span><a href="http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistics/inheritance/table12-2.pdf"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistics/inheritance/table12-2.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. This is where the net estate value before reliefs and exemptions are applied is potentially high enough to result in IHT liabilities.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Capital Gains Tax (CGT)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The latest published tables for information on individuals and trusts with Capital Gains were published on 31 October at </span><a href="http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistics/capital-gains-tax/table14-5.pdf"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/st</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">a</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">tistics/capital-gains-tax/table14-5.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">For the first time these included estimates of the number of taxpayers liable to CGT, amounts of Capital Gains on their disposals, and CGT liabilities by </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> country and English region. Unlike the estimates for receipts published at </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a href="http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/statistics/receipts/disagg-stats.pdf"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">http://w</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">w</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">w.h</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">m</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">rc.gov.uk/statistics/receipts/disagg-stats.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> the liability estimates were only for individuals, and the contribution from trusts was omitted. The published liability estimates also omitted any liabilities which were not reported via the self assessment system although this would only amount to a few million pounds.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">I hope you and other members of the Committee find this helpful.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">January 2014</span></p></div></body></html>